<div class="header mb-4">
	<h2>Getaway to the Islands of Hatteras and Ocracoke</h2>
</div>

<div class="content mb-4">
	<div>
		<p>Hatteras and Ocracoke are <em>the</em> remote and tranquil islands of the Outer Banks. This is where vacationers go to relax and unwind. It’s simple beach living at its greatest—complete with stunning natural scenery, quaint towns, and historic landmarks.</p>
		<p>On Hatteras Island, visit the famed lighthouse at the national seashore. Then, take some time to try some of the area's watersports such as paddleboarding or kite surfing. Fishing is a popular sport on Hatteras, and the Diamond Shoals off the island’s coast are perfect for hauling in a great catch.</p>
		<p>While on Ocracoke, immerse yourself in the island’s charm and history. Journey into Ocracoke Village to find eclectic shops, good food, and fun activities. While there, you’re sure to hear folklore involving one of history’s most storied pirates, Blackbeard, who once walked this island. Or, take a short boat ride to Portsmouth Island to see a coastal ghost town. Guests to Ocracoke Island are also rewarded with 12 miles of wide, tranquil beaches, unique shopping, and outstanding dining.</p>
	</div>
</div>